<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Crankcase, Crankshaft, Connecting
        Rods, And Pistons - Rear Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the rear cover is going to be removed, do not install the rear oil seal until the rear cover is
                    installed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200714" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3164.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Rear Oil Seal Installation Tool</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment Dowels</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Installation Tool</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear Crankcase Cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear oil seal installation tool onto the crankshaft flange. Install two rear
                seal alignment dowels.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply RTV sealant to the outer diameter of the crankshaft seal flange. Also apply a bead of
                RTV sealant around each bolt hole and the inside diameter of the bolt hole pattern to the crankshaft
                seal flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200715" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3163.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Rear Oil Seal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment Dowel</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft Seal Flange</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pilot Or Centering Tool</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the seal and wear sleeve assembly over the centering tool and position the seal
                retainer over the alignment dowels. Make sure the seal retainer and crankcase dowels align as the seal
                is being installed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200716" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3162.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Rear Oil Seal Driver</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Seal/Retainer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Installation Tool</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the driver over the centering tool. Tighten the forcing screw to drive the wear
                sleeve and rear seal into position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200717" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figEG3/EG3157.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Rear Oil Seal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Seal/Retainer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear Oil Seal Retainer Bolts (5)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retainer bolts. Tighten the bolts to the standard torque value.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
